This solution use a function flip() to literally flip array for K bits.
Applying Greedy algorithm, we go through the array, and once we see a "0", will perform a flip.
```
class Solution {
    private void flip(int[]A,int K,int i){
        for(int j=i;j<i+K;j++){
            A[j]=1-A[j];
        }
    }
    public int minKBitFlips(int[] A, int K) {
        int cnt=0;
        for(int i=0;i<A.length;i++){
            if(A[i]==0){
                if(i+K>A.length)return -1;
                flip(A,K,i);
                cnt++;
            }
        }
        return cnt;
    }
}
```

