# Pre-requisite
- Print modified array after multiple array range increment operations
- Range addition (Leetcode)

# Intuition
- We will process given array window by window of length k. 
- We iterate the given array from left to right and at any point of time, at ith index if we encouter current bit to be 0, then it should flip from 0 to 1. So we have to flip whole window starting from i and ending at i + k - 1.

---
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- After Applying all operation on valid windows (starting from `0th index` till `(n - k)th index`). 
- We will check that all bits are transferred to 1 or not. If all bit are transferred to 1 then answer will be `ans` or else ans will be `-1`.

---
# Code Walkthrough
- Gives the final bit after 'flips' flips on the bit
    - Example: bit = 0, flips = 5 => ans = 1
    - Example: bit = 1, flips = 5 => ans = 0
    - Example: bit = 0, flips = 4 => ans = 0
    - Example: bit = 1, flips = 4 => ans = 1
```
int finalbit(int bit, int flips)
{
    if (flips % 2 == 0)
        return bit;
    return !bit;
}
```
---
- pref[i] = for ith index, how many flips we have made
```
vector<int> pref(n + 1);
```
---
- For any index i, first of all we calculate the flips made on ith index from previous operations
- Now, if we have sufficient window (because we can only flip whole window of size 'k' according to given in question), then
    - after applying all flips on current bit, if current bit is 1. then we don't need to do any operation.
    - if current bit is 0. then we have to apply one operation. And though we have to flip whole window of size k starting from ith index, we will increment flip count in the range i to i + k - 1.

```

for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
{
    if (i)
        pref[i] += pref[i - 1];

    if (i < n - y + 1)
    {
        int flips = pref[i];
        int bit = finalbit(v[i], flips);

        if (bit == 1)
            continue;

        ans++;
        pref[i]++;
        pref[i + y]--;
    }
}
```
---
- After applying neccesary operations, we finally check the all bit. 
- If all bits are 1 then we return ans otherwise it is not possible to make array of all ones, so we return -1.
- This portion of the code is not neccesary neither the after vector, it can be computed in the above loop itself. But for the sack of simplicity of the code, i have done it separately.
```
int cnt = 0;
vector<int> after(n);
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
{
    after[i] = finalbit(v[i], pref[i]);
    cnt += (after[i] == 1);
}
return cnt == n ? ans : -1;
```

