solutions.content:
For each idx,
(number of flip + A[idx]) % 2 should be 1.

Then, how to calculate number of flip?

if (number of flip + A[idx]) % 2 is even, increase number of flip.
Also, we need to detect whether any of flipped segments is ended or not.
To check this, whenever flip occurs, update A[idx+K] += 2.

Then, for each index, idx, exactly one segment is over if A[idx] >= 2.
Check this for each start of an index.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int minKBitFlips(vector<int>& A, int K) {
        int flipped = 0;
        const int n = A.size();
        int ret = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
			// If one flipped segment is over, decrease flipped.
            if(A[i] > 1)    flipped -= 1;
			// If we need to flip this index,
            if((A[i]+flipped)%2 == 0) {
				// segment out of range.
                if(i + K > n)   return -1;
                flipped += 1;
				// we do not need to check the case, i + K == n 
                if(i + K < n)   A[i+K] += 2;
                ret++;
            }
        }
        return ret;
    }
};
```

